summary:
The Security Council,
 Reaffirming the purposes and principles of the Charter of the United Nations and its relevant resolutions, in particular its resolutions 1373 (2001) and 1566 (2004),
 Condemns without reservation the terrorist attacks in London on 7 July 2005, and regards any act of terrorism as a threat to peace and security;
 Expresses its deepest sympathy and condolences to the victims and their families, and to the people and Government of the United Kingdom;
 Urges all States to cooperate actively in efforts to find and bring to justice the perpetrators, organizers and sponsors of these acts, in accordance with their obligations under resolution 1373 (2001);
 Expresses its utmost determination to combat terrorism, in accordance with its responsibilities under the Charter of the United Nations.
